    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is a pretty minimal and isolated reproduction script:\r\n```\r\nconst util = require(\"util\");\r\nconst BN = require(\"BN.js\");\r\n\r\nutil.format(\"%d\", (new BN(10).pow(new BN(18)).subn(1)))\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe expected result is `\"999999999999999999\"`, but we get `\"1000000000000000000\"`.\r\n\r\nNote that this doesn't fix it, `util.format(\"%d\", (new BN(10).pow(new BN(18)).subn(1)).toString())`, as the string is also coerced into a `number`.\r\n",
